intel-vca2-host (2.3.26+ubuntu22.04.6) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Repackage Intel VCA 2.3.26 host stack for Ubuntu 22.04.
  * Keep v11 kernel modules with BlockIO enabled by default.
  * Keep DKMS vop.ko installation and plx87xx softdep ordering fix.
  * Disable the legacy hard NetworkManager boot guard in vcactl boot.
    NetworkManager now produces a warning only and no longer requires
    systemctl stop NetworkManager or --force for this check.
  * Keep host-side vca_csa blacklist; host uses vca_csm for /sys/class/vca.

